                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During his news conference of March 24, 1954, President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> commented on the impending Geneva
                    Conference and the battle of Dien Bien Phu. In the course of his remarks, he
                    described the Southeast Asian area as being of “the most transcendent
                    importance.”</p>
                <pb facs="1193" n="1161" xml:id="pg_1161"/>
                <p>For the record of the news conference of March 24, see <hi rend="italic">Public
                        Papers of the Presidents of the United States: <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                            >Dwight D. Eisenhower</persName>, 1954</hi>, pages 339–349.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
